                <note type="abstract">In his opening chapter Zucker takes up the question of whether there existed any Arabic translations made directly from the Hebrew text of the Bible prior to Saadiah and concludes that that there is no compelling evidence for such, either among the Qaraites (discussed specifically on pp. 3–4) or others (contra the present scholarly acceptance of pre-Saadianic and early non-Saadianic Judaeo-Arabic Bible translations). For additional references to the Qaraites by Zucker (most of which concern polemical aspects of Saadiah’s translation) see the index, s.v. קראים/קראי/קראות.</note>
